renthesis.\nAlternate approach: An expression of the form x squared plus b x plus c, where b and c are constants, can be factored if there are two values that add to give b and multiply to give c. In the given expression, b equals 3 and c equals negative 40. The values of negative 5 and 8 add to give 3 and multiply to give negative 40, so the expression can be factored as left parenthesis x minus 5 right parenthesis left parenthesis x plus 8 right parenthesis.\nChoice A is incorrect. This expression is equivalent to x squared plus 6 x minus 40, not x squared plus 3 x minus 40.\nChoice C is incorrect. This expression is equivalent to x squared minus 3 x minus 40, not x squared plus 3 x minus 40.\nChoice D is incorrect. This expression is equivalent to x squared minus 6 x minus 40, not x squared plus 3 x minus 40."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-112", "text": "A waiter receives tips from each customer. On average, the tip is 15% of the customer\u2019s bill. At this rate, which of the following is closest to the tip the waiter can expect when a customer has a bill that is $78.20?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["$8.00", "$10.00", "$12.00", "$14.00"], "correct_answer": "C", "difficulty": "easy", "explanation": "Choice C is correct. If the bill is $78.20, 15% of the bill can be found by multiplying 78.20 by the decimal conversion of 15%, 78.20 \u00d7 0.15 = $11.73. The exact amount $11.73 is closest in value to $12.00.Choices A, B, and D are incorrect and may be the result of errors when calculating 15% of the total $78.20."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-114", "text": "The function f is defined by f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals 8 StartRoot x EndRoot. For what value of x does f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals 48?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["6", "8", "36", "64"], "correct_answer": "C", "difficulty": "easy", "explanation": "Choice C is correct. It''s given that