n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n\nThe scatterplot has 10 data points.\nThe data points are in a linear pattern trending down from left to right.\nSelect data points have the following approximate coordinates:\n\n(0.8 comma 8.9)\n(2.8 comma 5.1)\n(4.1 comma 2.9)\n\nWhich of the following equations is the most appropriate linear model for the data shown in the scatterplot?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["y equals minus 1.9 x minus 10.1", "y equals minus 1.9 x plus 10.1", "y equals 1.9 x minus 10.1", "y equals 1.9 x plus 10.1"], "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "easy", "explanation": "Choice B is correct. The equation representing a linear model can be written in the form y equals a plus b x, or y equals b x plus a, where b is the slope of the graph of the model and left parenthesis 0 comma a right parenthesis is the y-intercept of the graph of the model. The scatterplot shows that as the x-values of the data points increase, the y-values of the data points decrease, which means the graph of an appropriate linear model has a negative slope. Therefore, b less than 0. The scatterplot also shows that the data points are close to the y-axis at a positive value of y. Therefore, the y-intercept of the graph of an appropriate linear model has a positive y-coordinate, which means a greater than 0. Of the given choices, only choice B, y equals minus 1.9 x plus 10.1, has a negative value for b, the slope, and a positive value for a, the y-coordinate of the y-intercept. \nChoice A is incorrect. The graph of this model has a y-intercept with a negative y-coordinate, not a positive y-coordinate.\nChoice C is incorrect. The graph of this model has a positive slope, not a negative slope, and a y-intercept with a negative y-coordinate, not a positive y-coordinate.\nChoice D is incorrect. The graph of this model has a positive slope, not a negative slope."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-116", "text": "x equals 5\ny equals x minus 8\nWhich of the following points left parenthesis x comma y right parenthesis is the solution to the given system of equations in the xy-plane?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["left parenthesis 0 comma 0 right parenthesis", "left parenthesis 5 comma negative 3 right parenthesis", "left parenthesis 5 comma negative 8 right parenthesis", "left parenthesis 5 comma 8 right parenthesis"], "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "easy", "explanation": "Choice B is correct. A solution to a system of equations in the xy-plane is a point left parenthesis x comma y right parenthesis that lies on the graph of each equation in the system. The first equation given is x equals 5. Substituting 5 for x in the second given equation yields y equals 5 minus 8, or y equals negative 3. It follows that in the xy-plane, the point left parenthesis 5 comma negative 3 right parenthesis lies on the graph of each equation in the system. Therefore, the solution to the given system of equations in the xy-plane is left parenthesis 5 comma negative 3 right parenthesis.\nChoice A is incorrect. The point left parenthesis 0 comma 0 right parenthesis doesn''t lie on the graph of either equation in the given system.\nChoice C is incorrect. The point left parenthesis 5 comma negative 8 right parenthesis doesn''t lie on the graph of the second equation in the given system.\nChoice D is incorrect. The point left parenthesis 5 comma 8 right parenthesis doesn''t lie on the graph of the second equation in the given system."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-118", "text": "The cost y, in dollars, for a manufacturer to make x rings is represented by the line shown.\n\n*{stroke-linecap:butt;stroke-linejoin:round;}\n \n\nThe line slants gradually up from left to right.\nThe line passes through the following points:\n\n(0 comma 100)\n(60 comma 175)\n(100 comma 225)\n\nWhat is the cost, in dollars, for the manufacturer to make 60 rings?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["100", "125", "175", "225"], "correct_answer": "C", "difficulty": "easy", "explanation": "Choice C is correct. The line shown represents the cost y, in dollars, for a manufacturer to make x rings. For the line shown, the x-axis represents the number of rings made by the manufacturer and the y-axis represents the cost, in dollars. Therefore, the cost, in dollars, for the manufacturer to make 60 rings is represented by the y-coordinate of the point on the line that has an x-coordinate of 60. The point on the line with an x-coordinate of 60 has a y-coordinate of 175. Therefore, the cost, in dollars, for the manufacturer to make 60 rings is 175.\nChoice A is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice B is incorrect. This is the cost, in dollars, for the manufacturer to make 20 rings.\nChoice D is incorrect. This is the cost, in dollars, for the manufacturer to make 100 rings."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-125", "text": "y equals x plus 4\nWhich table gives three values of x and their corresponding values of y for the given equation?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["x\ny\n\n0\n4\n\n1\n5\n\n2\n6", "x\ny\n\n0\n6\n\n1\n5\n\n2\n4", "x\ny\n\n0\n2\n\n1\n1\n\n2\n0", "x\ny\n\n0\n0\n\n1\n1\n\n2\n2"], "correct_answer": "A", "difficulty": "easy", "explanation": "Choice A is correct. Substituting 0 for x into the given equation yields y equals 0 plus 4, or y equals 4. Therefore, when x equals 0, the corresponding value of y for the given equation is 4. Substituting 1 for x into the given equation yields y equals 1 plus 4, or y equals 5. Therefore, when x equals 1, the corresponding value of y for the given equation is 5. Substituting 2 for x into the given equation yields y equals 2 plus 4, or y equals 6. Therefore, when x equals 2, the corresponding value of y for the given equation is 6. Of the choices given, only the table in choice A gives these three values of x and their corresponding values of y for the given equation.\nChoice B is incorrect. This table gives three values of x and their corresponding values of y for the equation y equals negative x plus 6.\nChoice C is incorrect. This table gives three values of x and their corresponding values of y for the equation y equals negative x plus 2.\nChoice D is incorrect. This table gives three values of x and their corresponding values of y for the equation y equals x."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-126", "text": "The densities of different concentrations of grape juice are shown in the scatterplot above. According to the trend shown by the data, which of the following is closest to the predicted density, in kilograms per cubic meter (kg/m3), for grape juice with a concentration of 60%?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["1,200", "1,250", "1,300", "1,350"], "correct_answer": "C", "difficulty": "easy", "explanation": "Choice C is correct. The data in the scatterplot show an increasing linear trend. The density when the juice concentration is 60% will be between the densities shown at about 53% and 67% concentration, or between about 1,255 and 1,340 kg/m3. Of the choices given, only 1,300 falls within this range.Choices A, B, and D are incorrect. These are the approximate densities of grape juice with a concentration of 45%, 55%, and 70%, respectively."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-135", "text": "y equals 76y equals x squared minus 5\nThe graphs of the given equations in the xy-plane intersect at the point left parenthesis x comma y right parenthesis. What is a possible value of x?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["negative StartFraction 76 Over 5 EndFraction", "negative 9", "5", "76"], "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "easy", "explanation": "Choice B is correct. Since the point left parenthesis x comma y right parenthesis is an intersection point of the graphs of the given equations in the xy-plane, the pair left parenthesis x comma y right parenthesis should satisfy both equations, and thus is a solution of the given system. According to the first equation, y equals 76. Substituting 76 in place of y in the second equation yields x squared minus 5 equals 76. Adding 5 to both sides of this equation yields x squared equals 81. Taking the square root of both sides of this equation yields two solutions: x equals 9 and x equals negative 9. Of these two solutions, only negative 9 is given as a choice.\nChoice A is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice C is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice D is incorrect. This is the value of coordinate y, rather than x, of the intersection point left parenthesis x comma y right parenthesis."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-136", "text": "A rocket contained 467,000 kilograms (kg) of propellant before launch. Exactly 21 seconds after launch, 362,105 kg of this propellant remained. On average, approximately how much propellant, in kg, did the rocket burn each second after launch?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["4,995", "17,243", "39,481", "104,895"], "correct_answer": "A", "difficulty": "easy", "explanation": "Choice A is correct. It\u2019s given that the rocket contained 467,000 kilograms left parenthesis kg right parenthesis of propellant before launch and had 362,105 kg remaining exactly 21 seconds after launch. Finding the difference between the amount, in kg, of propellant before launch and the remaining amount, in kg, of propellant after launch gives the amount, in kg, of propellant burned during the 21 seconds: 467,000 minus 362,105 equals 104,895. Dividing the amount of propellant burned by the number of seconds yields StartFraction 104,895 Over 21 EndFraction equals 4,995. Thus, an average of 4,995 kg of propellant burned each second after launch.\nChoice B is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice C is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice D is incorrect and may result from finding the amount of propellant burned, rather than the amount of propellant burned each second."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-137", "text": "A wind turbine completes 900 revolutions in 50 minutes. At this rate, how many revolutions per minute does this turbine complete?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["18", "850", "950", "1,400"], "correct_answer": "A", "difficulty": "easy", "explanation": "Choice A is correct. Dividing the number of revolutions by the number of minutes gives the number of revolutions the turbine completes per minute. It\u2019s given that the wind turbine completes 900 revolutions in 50 minutes. Therefore, at this rate, this turbine completes StartFraction 900 Over 50 EndFraction, or 18, revolutions per minute.\nChoice B is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice C is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice D is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-140", "text": "8 x equals 88\nWhat value of x is the solution to the given equation?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["11", "80", "96", "704"], "correct_answer": "A", "difficulty": "easy", "explanation": "Choice A is correct. Dividing both sides of the given equation by 8 yields x equals 11. Therefore, 11 is the solution to the given equation.\nChoice B is incorrect. This is the solution to the equation x plus 8 equals 88.\nChoice C is incorrect. This is the solution to the equation x minus 8 equals 88.\nChoice D is incorrect. This is the solution to the equation StartFraction x Over 8 EndFraction equals 88."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-141", "text": "Jay walks at a speed of 3 miles per hour and runs at a speed of 5 miles per hour. He walks for w hours and runs for r hours for a combined total of 14 miles. Which equation represents this situation?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["3 w plus 5 r equals 14", "one third w plus one fifth r equals 14", "one third w plus one fifth r equals 112", "3 w plus 5 r equals 112"], "correct_answer": "A", "difficulty": "easy", "explanation": "Choice A is correct. Since Jay walks at a speed of 3 miles per hour for w hours, Jay walks a total of 3 w miles. Since Jay runs at a speed of 5 miles per hour for r hours, Jay runs a total of 5 r miles. Therefore, the total number of miles Jay travels can be represented by 3 w plus 5 r. Since the combined total number of miles is 14, the equation 3 w plus 5 r equals 14 represents this situation.\nChoice B is incorrect and may result from conceptual errors.\nChoice C is incorrect and may result from conceptual errors.\nChoice D is incorrect and may result from conceptual errors."}]'::jsonb);
INSERT INTO sat_tests (title, description, test_type, difficulty, length, section, is_official, time_limit_minutes, questions) VALUES ('OpenSAT Math - Easy Set 3','Official-style SAT Math practice (Easy) from OpenSAT — image-free questions only.','math','easy','medium','math',true,38,'[{"id": "opensat-math-mcq-143", "text": "The equation 40 x plus 20 y equals 160 represents the number of sweaters, x, and number of shirts, y, that Yesenia purchased for dollar sign 160. If Yesenia purchased 2 sweaters, how many shirts did she purchase?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["3", "4", "8", "40"], "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "easy", "explanation": "Choice B is correct. It''s given that the equation 40 x plus 20 y equals 160 represents the number of sweaters, x, and the number of shirts, y, that Yesenia purchased for dollar sign 160. If Yesenia purchased 2 sweaters, the number of shirts she purchased can be calculated by substituting 2 for x in the given equation, which yields 40 left parenthesis 2 right parenthesis plus 20 y equals 160, or 80 plus 20 y equals 160. Subtracting 80 from both sides of this equation yields 20 y equals 80. Dividing both sides of this equation by 20 yields y equals 4. Therefore, if Yesenia purchased 2 sweaters, she purchased 4 shirts.\nChoice A is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice C is incorrect. This is the number of shirts Yesenia purchased if she purchased 0 sweaters.\nChoice D is incorrect. This is the price, in dollars, for each sweater, not the number of shirts Yesenia purchased."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-144", "text": "A cleaning service that cleans both offices and homes can clean at most 14 places per day. Which inequality represents this situation, where f is the number of offices and h is the number of homes?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["f plus h less than or equals 14", "f plus h greater than or equals 14", "f minus h less than or equals 14", "f minus h greater than or equals 14"], "correct_answer": "A", "difficulty": "easy", "explanation": "Choice A is correct. It''s given that the cleaning service cleans both offices and homes, where f is the number of offices and h is the number of homes the cleaning service can clean per day. Therefore, the expression f plus h represents the number of places the cleaning service can clean per day. It''s also given that the cleaning service can clean at most 14 places per day. Since f plus h represents the number of places the cleaning service can clean per day and the service can clean at most 14 places per day, it follows that the inequality f plus h less than or equals 14 represents this situation.\nChoice B is incorrect. This inequality represents a cleaning service that cleans at least 14 places per day.\nChoice C is incorrect. This inequality represents a cleaning service that cleans at most 14 more offices than homes per day.\nChoice D is incorrect. This inequality represents a cleaning service that cleans at least 14 more offices than homes per day."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-145", "text": "Which expression is equivalent to 256 w squared minus 676?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["left parenthesis 16 w minus 26 right parenthesis left parenthesis 16 w minus 26 right parenthesis", "left parenthesis 8 w minus 13 right parenthesis left parenthesis 8 w plus 13 right parenthesis", "left parenthesis 8 w minus 13 right parenthesis left parenthesis 8 w minus 13 right parenthesis", "left parenthesis 16 w minus 26 right parenthesis left parenthesis 16 w plus 26 right parenthesis"], "correct_answer": "D", "difficulty": "easy", "explanation": "Choice D is correct. The given expression follows the difference of two squares pattern, x squared minus y squared, which factors as left parenthesis x minus y right parenthesis left parenthesis x plus y right parenthesis. Therefore, the expre