plus 18 plus 90 equals 180, or s plus 108 equals 180. Subtracting 108 from both sides of this equation yields s equals 72. Therefore, if the measure of angle upper Q is 18 degrees, then the measure of angle upper S is 72 degrees.\nChoice A is incorrect. This is the measure of angle upper T.\nChoice C is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice D is incorrect. This is the sum of the measures of angle upper S and angle upper U."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-218", "text": "The table above shows a summary of 1,200 responses to a survey question. Based on the table, how many of those surveyed get most of their medical information from either a doctor or the Internet?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["865", "887", "912", "926"], "correct_answer": "C", "difficulty": "easy", "explanation": "Choice C is correct. According to the table, 63% of survey respondents get most of their medical information from a doctor and 13% get most of their medical information from the Internet. Therefore, 76% of the 1,200 survey respondents get their information from either a doctor or the Internet, and 76% of 1,200 is 912.Choices A, B, and D are incorrect. According to the table, 76% of survey respondents get their information from either a doctor or the Internet. Choice A is incorrect because 865 is about 72% (the percent of survey respondents who get most of their medical information from a doctor or from magazines/brochures), not 76%, of 1,200. Choice B is incorrect because 887 is about 74%, not 76%, of 1,200. Choice D is incorrect because 926 is about 77%, not 76%, of 1,200."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-219", "text": "s equals 40 plus 3 t\nThe equation gives the speed s, in miles per hour, of a certain car t seconds after it began to accelerate. What is the speed, in miles per hour, of the car 5 seconds after it began to accelerate?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["40", "43", "45", "55"], "correct_answer": "D", "difficulty": "easy", "explanation": "Choice D is correct. In the given equation, s is the speed, in miles per hour, of a certain car t seconds after it began to accelerate. Therefore, the speed of the car, in miles per hour, 5 seconds after it began to accelerate can be found by substituting 5 for t in the given equation, which yields s equals 40 plus 3 left parenthesis 5 right parenthesis, or s equals 55. Thus, the speed of the car 5 seconds after it began to accelerate is 55 miles per hour.\nChoice A is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice B is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice C is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-221", "text": "StartFraction x squared Over 25 EndFraction equals 36\nWhat is a solution to the given equation?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["6", "30", "450", "900"], "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "easy", "explanation": "Choice B is correct. Multiplying the left- and right-hand sides of the given equation by 25 yields x squared equals 900. Taking the square root of the left- and right-hand sides of this equation yields x equals 30 or x equals negative 30. Of these two solutions, only 30 is given as a choice.\nChoice A is incorrect. This is a solution to the equation x squared equals 36.\nChoice C is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice D is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-222", "text": "What is the perimeter, in inches, of a rectangle with a length of 4 inches and a width of 9 inches?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["13", "17", "22", "26"], "correct_answer": "D", "difficulty": "easy", "explanation": "Choice D is correct. The perimeter of a figure is equal to the sum of the measurements of the 