esis 5,184 right parenthesis, not f left parenthesis 144 right parenthesis."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-227", "text": "A band with 45 members has 11 members who play saxophone. If one band member is selected at random, what is the probability of selecting a band member who plays saxophone?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["one forty fifth", "StartFraction 11 Over 45 EndFraction", "StartFraction 34 Over 45 EndFraction", "StartFraction 45 Over 45 EndFraction"], "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "easy", "explanation": "Choice B is correct. The probability of an event occurring is the ratio of the number of favorable outcomes to the total number of possible outcomes. It\u2019s given that there are 45 band members, which is the total number of possible outcomes. It''s also given that there are 11 band members who play saxophone. Therefore, the number of favorable outcomes is 11. Thus, the probability of selecting a band member who plays saxophone is StartFraction 11 Over 45 EndFraction.\nChoice A is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice C is incorrect. This is the probability of selecting a band member who does not play saxophone.\nChoice D is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-229", "text": "x equals 10\ny equals x plus 21\nThe solution to the given system of equations is left parenthesis x comma y right parenthesis. What is the value of y?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["2.1", "10", "21", "31"], "correct_answer": "D", "difficulty": "easy", "explanation": "Choice D is correct. It''s given by the first equation in the given system of equations that x equals 10. Substituting 10 for x in the second equation in the given system yields y equals 10 plus 21, or y equals 31. Therefore, the value of y is 31.\nChoice A is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice B is incorrect. This is the value of x, not the value of y.\nChoice C is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-230", "text": "The function h is defined by h left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals x plus 200. What is the value of h left parenthesis 50 right parenthesis?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["200", "250", "10,000", "50,200"], "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "easy", "explanation": "Choice B is correct. Substituting 50 for x in the given function yields h left parenthesis 50 right parenthesis equals 50 plus 200, or h left parenthesis 50 right parenthesis equals 250. Therefore, the value of h left parenthesis 50 right parenthesis is 250.\nChoice A is incorrect. This is the value of h left parenthesis 0 right parenthesis.\nChoice C is incorrect. This is the value of h left parenthesis 9,800 right parenthesis.\nChoice D is incorrect. This is the value of h left parenthesis 50,000 right parenthesis."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-238", "text": "A gym charges its members a onetime dollar sign 36 enrollment fee and a membership fee of dollar sign 19 per month. If there are no charges other than the enrollment fee and the membership fee, after how many months will a member have been charged a total of dollar sign 188 at the gym?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["4", "5", "8", "10"], "correct_answer": "C", "difficulty": "easy", "explanation": "Choice C is correct. It\u2019s given that a gym charges its members a onetime dollar sign 36 enrollment fee and a membership fee of dollar sign 19 per month. Let x represent the number of months at the gym after which a member will have been charged a total of dollar sign 188. If there are no charges other than the enrollment fee and the membership fee, the equation 36 plus 19 x equals 188 can be used to represent this situation. Subtracting 36 from both sides of this equation yields 19 x equals 152. Dividing both sides of this equation by 19 yields x equals 8. Therefore, a member will have been charged a total of dollar sign 188 after 8 months at the gym.\nChoice A is incorrect. A member will have been charged a total of dollar sign left parenthesis 36 plus 19 times 4 right parenthesis, or dollar sign 112, after 4 months at the gym.\nChoice B is incorrect. A member will have been charged a total of dollar sign left parenthesis 36 plus 19 times 5 right parenthesis, or dollar sign 131, after 5 months at the gym.\nChoice D is incorrect. A member will have been charged a total of dollar sign left parenthesis 36 plus 19 times 10 right parenthesis, or dollar sign 226, after 10 months at the gym."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-240", "text": "Henry receives a dollar sign 60.00 gift card to pay for movies online. He uses his gift card to buy 3 movies for dollar sign 7.50 each. If he spends the rest of his gift card balance on renting movies for dollar sign 1.50 each, how many movies can Henry rent?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["10", "25", "35", "40"], "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "easy", "explanation": "Choice B is correct. It''s given that Henry uses his dollar sign 60.00 gift card to buy 3 movies for dollar sign 7.50 each. Therefore, Henry spends 3 left parenthesis dollar sign 7.50 right parenthesis, or dollar sign 22.50, of his dollar sign 60.00 gift card to buy 3 movies. After buying 3 movies with his dollar sign 60.00 gift card, Henry has a gift card balance of dollar sign 60.00 minus dollar sign 22.50, or dollar sign 37.50. It''s also given that Henry spends the rest of his gift card balance on renting movies for dollar sign 1.50 each. Therefore, Henry can rent StartFraction dollar sign 37.50 Over dollar sign 1.50 EndFraction, or 25, movies.\nChoice A is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice C is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice D is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-241", "text": "4 x equals 20\nminus 3 x plus y equals negative 7\nThe solution to the given system of equations is left parenthesis x comma y right parenthesis. What is the value of x plus y?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["negative 27", "negative 13", "13", "27"], "correct_answer": "C", "difficulty": "easy", "explanation": "Choice C is correct. It''s given that 4 x equals 20 and minus 3 x plus y equals negative 7 is a system of equations with a solution left parenthesis x comma y right parenthesis. Adding the second equation in the given system to the first equation yields 4 x plus left parenthesis minus 3 x plus y right parenthesis equals 20 plus left parenthesis negative 7 right parenthesis, which is equivalent to x plus y equals 13. Thus, the value of x plus y is 13. \nChoice A is incorrect. This represents the value of minus 2 left parenthesis x plus y right parenthesis minus 1.\nChoice B is incorrect. This represents the value of minus left parenthesis x plus y right parenthesis.\nChoice D is incorrect. This represents the value of 2 left parenthesis x plus y right parenthesis plus 1."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-243", "text": "Monarch butterflies can fly only with a body temperature of at least 55.0 degrees Fahrenheit left parenthesis degree upper F right parenthesis. If a monarch butterfly''s body temperature is 51.3 degree upper F, what is the minimum increase needed in its body temperature, in degree upper F, so that it can fly?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["1.3", "3.7", "5.0", "6.3"], "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "easy", "explanation": "Choice B is correct. It''s given that monarch butterflies can fly only with a body temperature of at least 55.0 degrees Fahrenheit left parenthesis degree upper F right parenthesis. Let x represent the minimum increase neede