he daily goal?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["4", "6", "20", "24"], "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "easy", "explanation": "Choice B is correct. It''s given that Ty plans to walk at an average speed of 4 kilometers per hour. The number of kilometers Ty will walk is determined by the expression 4 s, where s is the number of hours Ty walks. The given goal of at least 24 kilometers means that the inequality 4 s greater than or equals 24 represents the situation. Dividing both sides of this inequality by 4 gives s greater than or equals 6 , which corresponds to a minimum of 6 hours Ty must walk. \nChoice A is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice C is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice D is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-249", "text": "A kangaroo has a mass of 28 kilograms. What is the kangaroo''s mass, in grams? left parenthesis 1 kilogram equals 1,000 grams right parenthesis", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["28,000", "1,028", "972", "784"], "correct_answer": "A", "difficulty": "easy", "explanation": "Choice A is correct. It''s given that a kangaroo has a mass of 28 kilograms and that 1 kilogram is equal to 1,000 grams. Therefore, the kangaroo''s mass, in grams, is 28 kilograms left parenthesis StartFraction 1,000 grams Over 1 kilogram EndFraction right parenthesis, which is equivalent to 28,000 grams.\nChoice B is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice C is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice D is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-252", "text": "Which expression is equivalent to 9 x squared plus 5 x?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["x left parenthesis 9 x plus 5 right parenthesis", "5 x left parenthesis 9 x plus 1 right parenthesis", "9 x left parenthesis x plus 5 right parenthesis", "x squared left parenthesis 9 x plus 5 right parenthesis"], "correct_answer": "A", "difficulty": "easy", "explanation": "Choice A is correct. Since x is a factor of each term in the given expression, the expression is equivalent to x left parenthesis 9 x right parenthesis plus x left parenthesis 5 right parenthesis, or x left parenthesis 9 x plus 5 right parenthesis.\nChoice B is incorrect. This expression is equivalent to 45 x squared plus 5 x, not 9 x squared plus 5 x.\nChoice C is incorrect. This expression is equivalent to 9 x squared plus 45 x, not 9 x squared plus 5 x.\nChoice D is incorrect. This expression is equivalent to 9 x cubed plus 5 x squared, not 9 x squared plus 5 x."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-254", "text": "If 7 x equals 28, what is the value of 8 x?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["21", "32", "168", "224"], "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "easy", "explanation": "Choice B is correct. Dividing both sides of the given equation 7 x equals 28 by 7 yields x equals 4. Substituting 4 for x in the expression 8 x yields 8 left parenthesis 4 right parenthesis, which is equivalent to 32.\nChoice A is incorrect. This is the value of StartFraction 21 Over 4 EndFraction x.\nChoice C is incorrect. This is the value of 42 x.\nChoice D is incorrect. This is the value of 56 x."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-255", "text": "The members of a city council wanted to assess the opinions of all city residents about converting an open field into a dog park. The council surveyed a sample of 500 city residents who own dogs. The survey showed that the majority of those sampled were in favor of the dog park. Which of the following is true about the city council\u2019s survey?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["It shows that the majority of city residents are in favor of the dog park.", "The survey sample should have included more residents who are dog owners.", "The survey sample should have consisted entirely of residents who do not own dogs.", "The survey sample is biased because it is not representative of all city residents."], "correct_answer": "D", "difficulty": "easy", "explanation": "Choice D is correct. The members of the city council wanted to assess opinions of all city residents. To gather an unbiased sample, the council should have used a random sampling design to select subjects from all city residents. The given survey introduced a sampling bias because the 500 city residents surveyed were all dog owners. This sample is not representative of all city residents because not all city residents are dog owners.Choice A is incorrect because when the sampling method isn\u2019t random, there is no guarantee that the survey results will be reliable; hence, they cannot be generalized to the entire population. Choice B is incorrect because a larger sample of residents who are dog owners would not correct the sampling bias. Choice C is incorrect because a survey sample of entirely non\u2013dog owners would likely have a biased opinion, just as a sample of dog owners would likely have a biased opinion."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-256", "text": "x equals 8\ny equals x squared plus 8\nThe graphs of the equations in the given system of equations intersect at the point left parenthesis x comma y right parenthesis in the xy-plane. What is the value of y?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["8", "24", "64", "72"], "correct_answer": "D", "difficulty": "easy", "explanation": "Choice D is correct. Since the graphs of the equations in the given system intersect at the point left parenthesis x comma y right parenthesis, the point left parenthesis x comma y right parenthesis represents a solution to the given system of equations. The first equation of the given system of equations states that x equals 8. Subst