sponds to upper D, and upper B and upper E are right angles. The measure of angle upper A is 18 degree. What is the measure of angle upper F?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["18 degree", "72 degree", "90 degree", "162 degree"], "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "easy", "explanation": "Choice B is correct. It\u2019s given that triangle upper A upper B upper C is congruent to triangle upper D upper E upper F. Corresponding angles of congruent triangles are congruent and, therefore, have equal measure. It\u2019s given that angle upper A corresponds to angle upper D, and that the measure of angle upper A is 18 degree. It''s also given that the measures of angles upper B and upper E are 90 degree. Since these angles have equal measure, they are corresponding angles. It follows that angle upper C corresponds to angle upper F. Let x degree represent the measure of angle upper C. Since the sum of the measures of the interior angles of a triangle is 180 degree, it follows that 18 degree plus 90 degree plus x degree equals 180 degree, or 108 degree plus x degree equals 180 degree. Subtracting 108 degree from both sides of this equation yields x degree equals 72 degree. Therefore, the measure of angle upper C is 72 degree. Since angle upper C corresponds to angle upper F, it follows that the measure of angle upper F is also 72 degree.\nChoice A is incorrect. This is the measure of angle upper D, not the measure of angle upper F.\nChoice C is incorrect. This is the measure of angle upper E, not the measure of angle upper F.\nChoice D is incorrect. This is the sum of the measures of angles upper E and upper F, not the measure of angle upper F."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-327", "text": "How many of the males surveyed responded that they do not play a school sport?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["109", "252", "468", "688"], "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "easy", "explanation": "Choice B is correct. The table summarizes all 1,000 responses from the students surveyed. If 312 are males who play a sport, 220 are females who play a sport, and 216 are females who do not play a sport, then 1,000 \u2013 312 \u2013 220 \u2013 216 = 252 males who do not play a sport.Choices A, C, and D are incorrect. If 109 males who do not play a sport responded, then the table summary would be 109 + 312 + 220 + 216 = 857 total student responses rather than 1,000. If 468 males who do not play a sport responded, then the table summary would be 468 + 312 + 220 + 216 = 1,216 total student responses rather than 1,000. If 688 males who do not play a sport responded, then the table summary would be 688 + 312 + 220 + 216 = 1,436 total student responses rather than 1,000."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-333", "text": "The function f is defined by f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals one tenth x minus 2. What is the y-intercept of the graph of y equals f left parenthesis x right parenthesis in the xy-plane?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["left parenthesis negative 2 comma 0 right parenthesis", "left parenthesis 0 comma negative 2 right parenthesis", "left parenthesis 0 comma one tenth right parenthesis", "left parenthesis one tenth comma 0 right parenthesis"], "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "easy", "explanation": "Choice B is correct. The y-intercept of the graph of a function in the xy-plane is the point on the graph where x equals 0. It\u2032s given that f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals one tenth x minus 2. Substituting 0 for x in this equation yields f left parenthesis 0 right parenthesis equals one tenth left parenthesis 0 right parenthesis minus 2, or f left parenthesis 0 right parenthesis equals negative 2. Since it\u2032s given that y equals f left parenthesis x right parenthesis, it follows that y equals negative 2 when x equals 0. Therefore, the y-intercept of the graph of y equals f left parenthesis x right parenthesis in the xy-plane is left parenthesis 0 comma negative 2 right parenthesis.\nChoice A is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice C is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice D is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-335", "text": "In triangle upper A upper B upper C, the measure of angle upper B is 52 degree and the measure of angle upper C is 17 degree. What is the measure of angle upper A?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["21 degree", "35 degree", "69 degree", "111 degree"], "correct_answer": "D", "difficulty": "easy", "explanation": "Choice D is correct. The sum of the angle measures of a triangle is 180 degree. Adding the measures of angles upper B and upper C gives 52 plus 17 equals 69 degree. Therefore, the measure of angle upper A is 180 minus 69 equals 111 degree.\nChoice A is incorrect and may result from subtracting the sum of the measures of angles upper B and upper C from 90 degree, instead of from 180 degree.\nChoice B is incorrect and may result from subtracting the measure of angle upper C from the measure of angle upper B.\nChoice C is incorrect and may result from adding the measures of angles upper B and upper C but not subtracting the result from 180 degree."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-336", "text": "Line k is defined by y equals 3 x plus 15. Line j is perpendicular to line k in the xy-plane. What is the slope of line j?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["negative one third", "negative one twelfth", "negative one eighteenth", "negative one forty fifth"], "correct_answer": "A", "difficulty": "easy", "explanation": "Choice A is correct. It''s given that line j is perpendicular to line k in the xy-plane. It follows that the slope of line j is the opposite reciprocal of the slope of line k. The equation for line k is written in slope-intercept form y equals m x plus b, where m is the slope of the line and b is the y-coordinate of the y-intercept of the line. It follows that the slope of line k is 3. The opposite reciprocal of a number is negative 1 divided by the number. Thus, the opposite reciprocal of 3 is negative one third. Therefore, the slope of line j is negative one third.\nChoice B is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice C is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice D is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-337", "text": "If x equals 40, what is the value of x plus 6?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["34", "40", "46", "64"], "correct_answer": "C", "difficulty": "easy", "explanation": "Choice C is correct. It''s given that x equals 40. Adding 6 to both sides of this equation yields x plus 6 equals 40 plus 6, or x plus 6 equals 46. Therefore, the value of x plus 6 is 46.\nChoice A is incorrect. This is the value of x minus 6, not x plus 6.\nChoice B is incorrect. This is the value of x, not x plus 6.\nChoice D is incorrect. This is the value of x plus 24, not x plus 6."}, {"id": "opensat-math-mcq-338", "text": "A teacher is creating an assignment worth 70 points. The assignment will consist of questions worth 1 point and questions worth 3 points. Which equation represents this situation, where x represents the number of 1-point questions and y represents the number of 3-point questions?", "type": "multiple_choice", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "options": ["4 x y equals 70", "4 left parenthesis x plus y right parenthesis equals 70", "3 x plus y equals 70", "x plus 3 y equals 70"], "correct_answer": "D", "difficulty": "easy", "explanation": "Choice D is correct. Since x represents the number of 1-point questions and y represents the number of 3-point questions, the assignment is worth a total of 1 dot x plus 3 dot y, 