is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.\nChoice D is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors."}, {"id": "opensat-math-spr-468", "text": "4 x plus 5 equals 165\nWhat is the solution to the given equation?", "type": "grid_in", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "correct_answer": "40", "difficulty": "easy", "explanation": "The correct answer is 40. Subtracting 5 from both sides of the given equation yields 4 x equals 160. Dividing both sides of this equation by 4 yields x equals 40. Therefore, the solution to the given equation is 40."}, {"id": "opensat-math-spr-469", "text": "Line k is defined by y equals one fourth x plus 1. Line j is parallel to line k in the xy-plane. What is the slope of j?", "type": "grid_in", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "correct_answer": ".25, 1/4", "difficulty": "easy", "explanation": "The correct answer is one fourth. It''s given that line k is defined by y equals one fourth x plus 1. It''s also given that line j is parallel to line k in the xy-plane. A line in the xy-plane represented by an equation in slope-intercept form y equals m x plus b has a slope of m and a y-intercept of left parenthesis 0 comma b right parenthesis. Therefore, the slope of line k is one fourth. Since parallel lines have equal slopes, the slope of line j is one fourth. Note that 1/4 and .25 are examples of ways to enter a correct answer."}, {"id": "opensat-math-spr-476", "text": "*{stroke-linecap:butt;stroke-linejoin:round;}\n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n 