arenthesis 8 right parenthesis plus 10, or y equals 50. Therefore, the value of y is 50 when x equals 8."}, {"id": "opensat-math-spr-497", "text": "A list of 10 data values is shown.\n6, 8, 16, 4, 17, 26, 8, 5, 5, 5\nWhat is the mean of these data?", "type": "grid_in", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "correct_answer": "10", "difficulty": "easy", "explanation": "The correct answer is 10. The mean of a data set is calculated by dividing the sum of the data values by the number of data values in the data set. For this data set, the mean can be calculated as StartFraction 6 plus 8 plus 16 plus 4 plus 17 plus 26 plus 8 plus 5 plus 5 plus 5 Over 10 EndFraction, which is equivalent to StartFraction 100 Over 10 EndFraction, or 10."}, {"id": "opensat-math-spr-499", "text": "The function g is defined by g left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals 6 x. For what value of x is g left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals 54?", "type": "grid_in", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "correct_answer": "9", "difficulty": "easy", "explanation": "The correct answer is 9. It\u2019s given that g left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals 6 x. Substituting 54 for g left parenthesis x right parenthesis in the given function yields 54 equals 6 x. Dividing both sides of this equation by 6 yields x equals 9. Therefore, the value of x when g left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals 54 is 9."}, {"id": "opensat-math-spr-500", "text": "The function f is defined by the equation f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals 7 x plus 2. What is the value of f left parenthesis x right parenthesis when x equals 4?", "type": "grid_in", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "correct_answer": "30", "difficulty": "easy", "explanation": "The correct answer is 30. The value of f left parenthesis x right parenthesis when x equals 4 can be found by substituting 4 for x in the given equation f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals 7 x plus 2. This yields f left parenthesis 4 right parenthesis equals 7 left parenthesis 4 right parenthesis plus 2, or f left parenthesis 4 right parenthesis equals 30. Therefore, when x equals 4, the value of f left parenthesis x right parenthesis is 30."}, {"id": "opensat-math-spr-508", "text": "The y-intercept of the graph of y equals minus 6 x minus 32 in the xy-plane is left parenthesis 0 comma y right parenthesis. What is the value of y?", "type": "grid_in", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "correct_answer": "-32", "difficulty": "easy", "explanation": "The correct answer is negative 32. It\u2019s given that the y-intercept of the graph of y equals minus 6 x minus 32 is left parenthesis 0 comma y right parenthesis. Substituting 0 for x in this equation yields y equals minus 6 left parenthesis 0 right parenthesis minus 32, or y equals negative 32. Therefore, the value of y that corresponds to the y-intercept of the graph of y equals minus 6 x minus 32 in the xy-plane is negative 32."}, {"id": "opensat-math-spr-509", "text": "The y-intercept of the graph of 12 x plus 2 y equals 18 in the xy-plane is left parenthesis 0 comma y right parenthesis. What is the value of y?", "type": "grid_in", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "correct_answer": "9", "difficulty": "easy", "explanation": "The correct answer is 9. It''s given that the y-intercept of the graph of 12 x plus 2 y equals 18 in the xy-plane is left parenthesis 0 comma y right parenthesis. Substituting 0 for x in the equation 12 x plus 2 y equals 18 yields 12 left parenthesis 0 right parenthesis plus 2 y equals 18, or 2 y equals 18. Dividing both sides of this equation by 2 yields y equals 9. Therefore, the value of y is 9."}, {"id": "opensat-math-spr-510", "text": "The function f is defined by f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals 4 x. For what value of x does f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals 8?", "type": "grid_in", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "correct_answer": "2", "difficulty": "easy", "explanation": "The correct answer is 2. Substituti