 7. It\u2019s given that the x-intercept of the graph shown is left parenthesis x comma 0 right parenthesis. The graph passes through the point left parenthesis 7 comma 0 right parenthesis. Therefore, the value of x is 7."}, {"id": "opensat-math-spr-613", "text": "StartAbsoluteValue x minus 2 EndAbsoluteValue equals 9\nWhat is one possible solution to the given equation?", "type": "grid_in", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "correct_answer": "11, -7", "difficulty": "easy", "explanation": "The correct answer is 11 or negative 7. By the definition of absolute value, if StartAbsoluteValue x minus 2 EndAbsoluteValue equals 9, then x minus 2 equals 9 or x minus 2 equals negative 9. Adding 2 to both sides of the equation x minus 2 equals 9 yields x equals 11. Adding 2 to both sides of the equation x minus 2 equals negative 9 yields x equals negative 7. Thus, the given equation, StartAbsoluteValue x minus 2 EndAbsoluteValue equals 9, has two possible solutions, 11 and negative 7. Note that 11 and -7 are examples of ways to enter a correct answer."}, {"id": "opensat-math-spr-614", "text": "StartAbsoluteValue x minus 5 EndAbsoluteValue equals 10\nWhat is one possible solution to the given equation?", "type": "grid_in", "topic": "math", "section": "math", "correct_answer": "15, -5", "difficulty": "easy", "explanation": "The correct answer is 15 or negative 5. By the definition of absolute value, if StartAbsoluteValue x minus 5 EndAbsoluteValue equals 10, then x minus 5 equals 10 or x minus 5 equals negative 10. Adding 5 to both sides of the first equation yields x equals 15. Adding 5 to both sides of the second equation yields x equals negative 5. Thus, the given equation has two possible solutions, 15 and negative 5. Note that 15 and -5 are examples of ways to enter a correct answer."}, {"id": "opensat-math-spr-617", "text": "A special camera is used for underwater ocean research. When the camera is at a depth of 58 fathoms, what is the camera''s depth in feet? left paren